Key Match Events: Nico Hoerner had two hits and scored two runs, and the Chicago Cubs beat the sloppy Washington Nationals 5-3 on Saturday for their fifth straight win.
The Cubs scored 4 runs in the 5th inning to take the lead.
Catcher C. Bethancourt grounded out to catcher, Hoerner scored on throwing error by catcher Millas in the 7th inning.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cubs won their fifth straight game.
The Cubs took the current series 3-0.
Others: Javier Assad pitched 6.0 IP, 8 H, 3 ER, 4 K, 2 BB for the Cubs.
DJ Herz pitched 4.2 IP, 3 H, 4 ER, 5 K, 2 BB for the Nationals.
